olive oil
1 garlic
1 capsicum
1 packet green beans
½ packet char siu paste
1 packet oyster sauce
1 tbs soy sauce
drizzle vinegar (rice wine or white wine)
1 packet udon noodles
1 packet beef strips
1 packet Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 packet ginger paste
1 sachet sesame seeds

• Boil the kettle. Finely chop garlic. Thinly slice capsicum.  Trim green beans and cut into thirds.
• In a small bowl, combine char siu paste (see ingredients), oyster sauce, the soy sauce, vinegar and a dash of water. Set aside.

Little cooks: Take charge by combining the sauces!

• Half-fill a medium saucepan with boiling water. Cook udon noodles over medium-high heat until tender, 1-2 minutes.
• In the last minute of cook time, gently stir noodles with a fork to separate. Drain, rinse and set aside.

• Discard any liquid from beef strips packaging.
• Heat a large frying pan over high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. When oil is hot, cook beef strips in batches, tossing, until browned and cooked through, 1-2 minutes.
• Return all beef to the pan, then add sweet soy seasoning, shredded cabbage mix, capsicum, garlic and ginger paste. Cook until tender and fragrant, 3-4 minutes.
• Add cooked udon noodles and char siu sauce mixture and cook, tossing, until thickened, 1-2 minutes.

• Divide char siu beef udon noodles between bowls.
• Sprinkle over sesame seeds. Enjoy!